@page "/tyne/overview"

<TyneTitle Value="Tyne Overview" />

<DocSection>
    <Title>Introduction</Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            The Tyne core library provides a framework for creating ASP.NET Core systems. It is designed for use in Blazor Server apps.
        </MudText>
    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>

<DocSection>
    <Title>
        <MudLink Href="/tyne/actions" Typo="Typo.h5">
            Actions
        </MudLink>
    </Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            At it's simplest, an action takes some @Keyword("TInput") and produces a @Keyword("TOutput"). When executed, an action returns a @Keyword("Task<Result<TOutput>>").
            See the <MudLink Href="/tyne/result">@Keyword("Result")</MudLink> type for more information.
        </MudText>
    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>

<DocSection>
    <Title>
        <MudLink Href="/tyne/queries" Typo="Typo.h5">
            Queries
        </MudLink>
    </Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Queries are an extension of an @Keyword("IAction") which takes an @Keyword("ISearchQuery") and returns a @Keyword("SearchResult").
        </MudText>
    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>

<DocSection>
    <Title>
        <MudLink Href="/tyne/results" Typo="Typo.h5">
            Results
        </MudLink>
    </Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            The @Keyword("Result") type encapsulates the result of an @Keyword("IAction"). @Keyword("Result") has a @Keyword("Metadata") property which stores metadata about the action's result, such as errors or messages to the user.
            When an action was successful, @Keyword("Result.Value") will hold the value generated by the action.
        </MudText>

    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>

<DocSection>
    <Title>
        <MudLink Href="/tyne/unit" Typo="Typo.h5">
            Unit
        </MudLink>
    </Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            The @Keyword("Unit") type indicates the absence of a specific value; the unit type has only a single value, which acts as a placeholder when no other value exists or is needed.
            See the <MudLink Href="/tyne/unit">unit documentation</MudLink> for more information about it's design and usage.
        </MudText>

    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>

<DocSection>
    <Title>
        <MudLink Href="/tyne/utilities" Typo="Typo.h5">
            Utilities
        </MudLink>
    </Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Tyne exposes some of the miscellaneous utilities it uses internally.
        </MudText>
    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>

<DocSection>
    <Title>
        <MudLink Href="/tyne/validation" Typo="Typo.h5">
            Validation
        </MudLink>
    </Title>
    <ChildContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Tyne's validation is build on <MudLink Href="https://docs.fluentvalidation.net/en/latest/">FluentValidation</MudLink>.
        </MudText>
    </ChildContent>
</DocSection>


